      "text": ".@fema and @MSEMA are working around the clock tirelessly to support Mississippians affected by Winter Storm Fern, and we are deeply grateful for their leadership and coordination. \n\nIf you are in need of assistance, please reach out to your county Emergency Management Agency coordinator. They are the first line of support on the ground and can connect you with supplies, help, and the most up-to-date information.\n\n@POTUS, @Sec_Noem, Governor @tatereeves, @MississippiDOT, the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, the National Guard, our electric coops, the road crews, the linemen, and the first responders serving on the front lines all deserve our overwhelming thanks.\n\nWe will get through this together. Your hard work and dedication do not go unnoticed.\n\nStay updated here:\nhttps://t.co/Q23WckHj9J",
      "text_resolved": ".@fema and @MSEMA are working around the clock tirelessly to support Mississippians affected by Winter Storm Fern, and we are deeply grateful for their leadership and coordination. \n\nIf you are in need of assistance, please reach out to your county Emergency Management Agency coordinator. They are the first line of support on the ground and can connect you with supplies, help, and the most up-to-date information.\n\n@POTUS, @Sec_Noem, Governor @tatereeves, @MississippiDOT, the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, the National Guard, our electric coops, the road crews, the linemen, and the first responders serving on the front lines all deserve our overwhelming thanks.\n\nWe will get through this together. Your hard work and dedication do not go unnoticed.\n\nStay updated here:\nhttps://www.msema.org/get-assistance/disaster-resources/disasters/january-2026-winter-weather",
